First Lady Michelle Obama will be delivering commencement addresses at Virginia Tech, North Carolina A&T, and Oregon State University. At Virginia Tech, she was inspired by the resilience of the student body and community. At North Carolina A&T, she will be speaking at a historically black college and university (HBCU). At Oregon State University, she will be addressing graduates who have been recognized for their efforts to promote healthy communities. Mrs. Obama has previously spoken at various other graduations, including the University of California Merced, the University of Arkansas at Pine Bluff, and West Point.